I think you‚Äôve hit the nail on the head with the 100,000 tiny files comment. rsync would take a significant amount of time to process each file, and even comparing them for changes would be an expensive process. Whereas the method used for the WSL export is probably very good at wrapping up lots of tiny files efficiently, as it‚Äôs compressing them together into a single file, not processing each individually and comparing each copy.

Trevor R suggested using Robocopy ‚Äì you could try using that from Win instead of rsync in Linux. There is a chance it‚Äôd handle the tiny files better, although it might not.

You may just find that wsl ‚Äìexport is the best option for you.

